# UI Design System Rules

- Source tokens live in the shared UI package styles.
- Use CSS variables for colors, spacing, radii, typography, and shadows.
- Keep white surfaces, dark text, and a clear primary accent.
- Avoid dark themes, glass effects, and hardcoded one-off color values.
- Shared UI components should be reusable across apps and exported cleanly from the UI package.
- Prefer small, composable components over app-specific widgets inside the shared package.
